description:
This is a 31 minute workout called '4-7-8 Calm Breathing Exercise | 30 Minutes Custom Relaxation | Anxiety Relief | Pranayama Exercise' from the channel Hands-On Meditation.
The workout falls under Rest/Breathing exercises and Rest/Meditation.
It's suitable for Beginner and Intermediate fitness levels.
The workout has a The Deep Recharge and The Sleep Prep vibe.
The technique difficulty is Beginner.
The effort required is Light.

Original workout description: Enjoy the deepest relaxation and increase lung capacity with this customizable 30 minute version of the 4-7-8 breathing technique. Just practice for a length of time that works best for you (up to 30 minutes). The breaths gradually slow and extend to an ideal calming pace.

4-7-8 rhythmic breathing is a core part of many meditation and yoga practices as it promotes relaxation and can also be used to help you fall asleep in a shorter period of time. The goal is to calm your sympathetic nervous system, which controls the fight-or-flight response. 

NOTE: In this video, the 4-7-8 counting does not follow seconds (the pace is purposefully slower). There are other versions of the 4-7-8 exercise on this channel that have a faster breathing pace and versions that have a slower breathing pace. You should try them all to learn what works best for you.
